ChargeFan1, I dont want to get in a sentence by sentence dismantling of arguments...<br>
<br>
You dont think that more people or even an equal number of people believe in the bible's account of creationism than dont, do you?  Far more people follow other religions or none at all.<br>
<br>
Since the story of creation only allows for a very young earth, then I would have to say that scientific evidence does refute the creation as represented in the bible.<br>
<br>
&quot;Or are you accepting current theories concerning evolution.&quot;<br>
<br>
Let's be clear here.  A scientific theory is considered fact by an accumulation of evidence.  The Theory of Relativity is a theory because there is proof.  The Theory of Evolution is a theory because there is proof.  If there was no proof, just conjecture, it would be a hypothesis.<br>
<br>
As stated, evidence of land at one time being covered by water is common, many religions have a flood myth.  Does &quot;evidence&quot; of a world wide flood lend as much credence to Hinduism in your eyes?  Or is it only evidence that proves the Christian version.  Every ancient culture was free to interpret the evidence as they saw fit.  But only the Christians got it right, right?  Hypocrisy.<br>
<br>
What do the egyptians have to do with anything.  Misdirection.  They had their own myths, their own science, just as the greeks.<br>
<br>
I began by stating that the bible was not a reputable source of historical information.  Not that is was all lies.  Troy is absolutely a real place and was found using biblical references.  So what?  New York is a real place, am I to believe Escape from New York is real?  Both are works of fiction.<br>
<br>
Boston is sinking and it doesn't matter when you date submerged man made structures, glacial melt is not the only way for them to end up under water.<br>
<br>
As for insulting those with faith...  I'm sure millions of people during the crusades felt insulted.  How you handle your belief is a totally seperate matter, you I'm sure would not use religion as an excuse to oppress.  But the fact is that many do.  <br>
<br>
Your post, ChargerFan, was not up when I began answering Matt4Zion's. sorry for the confusion.<br>
