If you want to speak of hypocrisy, perhaps that you can start with modern historians.  For an example, much of what we know about the Egyptians are derived from the hieroglyphs.  There is on in particular that outlines the origin of the Egyptians, back to what they called the 'First Time'.  Modern historians have deduced that some of it is fact, and some is fiction.  The reason?  The timelines.  Some of it doesn't fit into their paradigm of history.  I believe Herodotus visited Egypt in antiquity and spoke (at that time) of how ancient the people of Egypt were.<br>
