<br>
Your beliefs dont make you anything other than &quot;you&quot;.  The number of times earth has been created or destroyed is moot.  Science has an estimated age of the earth and with a few exceptions, believers in the bible's account contend that it is far younger.<br>
<br>
The word &quot;Theory&quot; in science has a specific meaning that is opposite to its regular use.  I could bang my head against a wall in frustration, that the use of this word was decided upon, but it is out of my hands.  &quot;Theory&quot; is commonly used to describe an idea that is based on speculation.  As in &quot; I have a theory that Elvis is alive.&quot;  In science however &quot;Theory&quot; is an explanation based on observation and reasoning.  The observation part is important to us,  it constitutes observational evidence than is recordable and repeatable ie/ evidence.   A scientific &quot;Theory&quot; is a Theory because proof exists.  I have already given proof of our own evolution.  We have the remnants of an organ that is no longer needed because of changes in our diets and the changes in other systems in our body.  Our appendix is no longer needed, other parts of your body provide the function that it was once required for.<br>
<br>
Your beliefs are your beliefs, and you are free to follow them. The bottom line is that if the proof of your beliefs lies in disproving mine, you will have a hard time.  The same &quot;Theories&quot; and evidence of them have led to many other scientific truths that you benefit from on a daily basis.  The theory of relativity lead to nuclear power that provides electricity for many cities.  And the theory evolution lead to genetic studies in diseases, agriculture, and medicine.<br>
